headline: U.S. Private-Equity Firm I Squared Leads Race for KKR’s Singapore Logistics Asset
summary: The U.S. private-equity firm has emerged as a leading contender to acquire KKR’s Singapore-based supply chain and logistics company, valued at up to $1.5 billion, people familiar with the process said.
